;; Implement LLM Streaming Hookup
;; ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
;;
;; This workflow implements real-time token streaming for LLM interactions,
;; enabling users to see LLM output as it's generated rather than waiting for
;; complete responses.
;;
;; Usage:
;;   mf run examples/workflows/implement-llm-streaming-hookup.edn

{:workflow/spec-version "1.0.0"
 :workflow/type :standard-sdlc
 :workflow/version "2.0.0"

 :title "Implement LLM Streaming Hookup"
 :description
 "Wire up token streaming in agents and workflow runner to enable real-time output visibility.

  Current state:
  - LLM component has streaming API (complete-stream, chat-stream) ✅
  - Agents use synchronous llm/chat ❌
  - Workflow runner doesn't pass streaming callbacks ❌

  The implementation should:
  1. Add streaming support to agent protocol (optional :on-chunk callback in opts)
  2. Update agent implementations to use chat-stream when :on-chunk provided
  3. Wire streaming callbacks in workflow runner to display agent progress
  4. Add tests for streaming behavior in agents
  5. Ensure backward compatibility (streaming is opt-in via context/opts)"

 :intent
 {:type "feature"
  :description "Enable real-time streaming of LLM token output to provide progress visibility
  during long-running operations. Currently, LLM interactions are synchronous - users must
  wait for the entire response before seeing any output. This creates poor UX for workflows
  that take minutes to complete.

  Context: During the pre-commit discipline gate workflow, we had no visibility into what
  miniforge was doing for 4+ minutes. The streaming implementation exists conceptually
  (PR #96 mentioned it) but isn't wired up in the public API or CLI runner.

  This implementation will enable:
  - Real-time progress monitoring during workflow execution
  - Better debugging visibility into agent reasoning
  - Improved user experience for long-running operations
  - Foundation for interactive agent sessions"}

 :constraints
 ["Maintain backward compatibility (streaming is opt-in, not default)"
  "Check for :on-chunk in opts/context before using streaming"
  "Use existing llm/chat-stream API (already implemented)"
  "Handle cases where :on-chunk is nil (fall back to sync)"
  "Add tests for both streaming and non-streaming agent behavior"
  "Document streaming usage in agent docstrings"
  "Ensure all existing tests pass without modification"
  "Follow existing agent architecture patterns"
  "No breaking changes to agent protocol"
  "CLI flag: --streaming to enable for mf run command"]

 :acceptance-criteria
 ["Agents check for :on-chunk in opts/context"
  "When :on-chunk present, agents use llm/chat-stream instead of llm/chat"
  "When :on-chunk absent, agents use llm/chat (existing behavior)"
  "Workflow runner creates :on-chunk callback when streaming enabled"
  "Callback prints formatted output: \"[agent-name] chunk-content\""
  "CLI accepts --streaming flag for mf run command"
  "Unit tests verify agents use streaming when :on-chunk provided"
  "Integration test shows real-time output during workflow execution"
  "Backward compatibility: all existing tests pass without changes"
  "Documentation explains streaming usage in agent rich comments"]

 :context
 {:supporting-docs
  ["components/llm/src/ai/miniforge/llm/interface.clj"
   "components/llm/src/ai/miniforge/llm/interface/protocols/llm_client.clj"
   "components/llm/src/ai/miniforge/llm/protocols/impl/llm_client.clj"
   "components/llm/src/ai/miniforge/llm/protocols/records/llm_client.clj"
   "components/workflow/src/ai/miniforge/workflow/runner.clj"]

  :current-state
  "LLM component HAS streaming (merged in feat/llm-token-streaming):
  - Protocol has: complete-stream* [this request on-chunk] ✅
  - Public API has: complete-stream, chat-stream ✅
  - Implementation processes output line-by-line ✅
  - Tests verify streaming callbacks work ✅

  What's MISSING:
  - Agents use llm/chat (sync) instead of llm/chat-stream
  - Workflow runner doesn't provide :on-chunk callbacks to agents
  - No way to opt into streaming during workflow execution
  - Users can't see agent reasoning in real-time"

  :technical-approach
  "Wire streaming from LLM component → agents → workflow runner:

  1. Agent implementation changes:
     - Check for :on-chunk in opts/context
     - If present, use llm/chat-stream instead of llm/chat
     - Pass :on-chunk callback through
     - Affects: planner.clj, implementer.clj, tester.clj, reviewer.clj

  2. Workflow runner integration:
     - Create on-chunk callback that prints to stdout
     - Format: \"[phase-name/agent-name] chunk-content\"
     - Pass callback in agent context via :on-chunk key
     - Add :enable-streaming? flag to workflow runner opts

  3. Backward compatibility:
     - Streaming is opt-in via :enable-streaming? flag
     - Default behavior unchanged (synchronous)
     - Existing tests continue to pass

  4. User-facing changes:
     - mf run --streaming workflow.edn
     - Shows real-time agent output during execution"}

 :meta-loop-monitoring
 {:test-with-callbacks
  "Create test that verifies :on-token is called for each output chunk"

  :test-error-handling
  "Verify :on-error is called when CLI command fails"

  :test-backward-compatibility
  "Ensure existing complete/chat tests still pass unchanged"

  :integration-test
  "Run a workflow with streaming enabled and verify output appears incrementally"}

 :evidence-requirements
 ["Streaming implementation passes all unit tests"
  "Integration test shows incremental output during execution"
  "Existing tests continue to pass (no regressions)"
  "Documentation clearly explains streaming vs non-streaming usage"
  "Code follows existing component architecture patterns"]}
